---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import PageHeader from "../components/PageHeader.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Download Paunix Guard for Windows">
  <PageHeader
    eyebrow="Download"
    title="Install Paunix Guard for Windows."
    lead="Use the setup installer for the best experience. It enables Velopack-managed updates and avoids the confusing package choices shown on raw release pages."
  />

  <section class="page-shell section download-layout">
    <div class="download-box">
      <h2>Windows installer</h2>
      <p>Recommended path for every normal user. After setup, create a PIN and Paunix Guard will continue directly into the app.</p>
      <div class="download-meta">
        <div><span>File</span><strong>PaunixGuard-win-Setup.exe</strong></div>
        <div><span>Version</span><strong>0.1.2</strong></div>
        <div><span>Auto-update</span><strong>Velopack</strong></div>
      </div>
      <div class="button-row">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/download/windows">Download for Windows</a>
        <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/changelog">View changelog</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <aside class="text-panel">
      <h2>SmartScreen note</h2>
      <p>Early builds are not code-signed yet, so Windows may show a SmartScreen warning. Code signing is planned; the current installer remains source-available and has public release notes.</p>
      <p>Paunix Guard does not need an internet connection for core protection after install.</p>
    </aside>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
